T~L~990~-305~0~#000080~Arial~~~~~comment~To measure battery voltage.
Analog reference is set to 1.1V.
6.0V battery voltage will result in
0.769V on the ADC1 input.
This will result in a reading of
715 on a 0..1023 scale.~1~start~gge10299~0~pinpart

T~L~70~-355~0~#000080~Arial~~~~~comment~With potentiometer set to 4K8:
When the battery voltage is 5x1.35 = 6.75V
the reference voltage of the TL431CZ
becomes 2.5V which means it will shunt
the charge current to ground.
This will prevent overcharging of the
NiMH batteries.
With the potentiometer one can vary the
max. battery voltage from appr. 5.55V to 8.05V.~1~start~gge13784~0~pinpart

T~L~720~-180~0~#000080~Arial~~~~~comment~No level converter for RPi needed if:
- ATMEGA328P is the I2C slave and has the
  internal pullups disabled.
- RPi is the I2C master and has the
  internal pullups to 3.3V enabled.
Do not connect I2C devices with pullups
to 5V as the RPi cannot handle this.~1~start~gge15121~0~pinpart

T~L~885~-685~0~#000080~Arial~~~~~comment~Shottky diode to increase RPi voltage with appr. 0.30 V.
